		<td><b>[SOLVED]Family Basic Cartridge Repro, need help</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'm trying to make a Family Basic Cartridge Reproduction. Recently I've done some lessons and prepared some parts and chips for this work. Before I start, I want to make sure that my direction will not lead me to a dead end:<br /><br />I have 2 AT29C256 flash chips. Is it possible to use them as PRG/CHR roms and program them using Kazzo? There is no configration for this chip in Kazzo's software, but I wonder maybe it can be implemented according to <a href="https://zh.osdn.net/projects/unagi/wiki/flash_device_en" class="postlink">this article</a>?<br /><br />If this chip is OK then I'll continue to make the pcb and try to do soldering work and finally the chip programming.<br /><br />I'm eagerly waiting for you guys' advices. Thank you!

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
