	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Thank you for your reply, lidnariq. I know it is an NROM with PRG RAM.<br />I've read the <a href="http://unagi.osdn.jp/cgi-bin/hiki/hiki.cgi?device_flashmeory" class="postlink">documents</a> of Kazzo and learned something on how to choose flash chips. It seems AM29F040 is the best choice, which benifits from its Command Address Width and something else. However I don't have this chip, neither do I have any kind metioned in the document.<br />I only have AT29C256. The capacity is 32KB, suitable for NROM with little waste.<br />Well, the most important thing is that I don't know whether this chip is supported by Kazzo. I want to ask if you guys had ever used this chip could you please tell me whether it can be programmed like other recommended flash?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
